In the sleepy village of Liora, tucked between silver forests and starlit hills, a peculiar flame burned in the center squareÔÇöblue, ever-whispering, and cold to the touch. No one knew who lit it or why it never died. Elara, a curious orphan with a streak of moon-white hair, visited it every night. One evening, the flame whispered her name.

Following the whisper, Elara uncovered a hidden scroll beneath the floorboards of the old bakery where she lived. It was a map inked in stardust, pointing beyond the forest, past the Weeping Lake, to a place called The Shattered Spire. Beside it, a single phrase: ÔÇ£He who touches Moonfire may mend the sky.ÔÇØ

fields.chapter_title: Chapter 3: The Fox and the Blade
fields.chapter_content: Elara journeyed into the wilds, where she met a talking fox named Korrin, a trickster bound by ancient magic. He offered her a trade: a silver blade forged from fallen stars, in exchange for a single memory. She gave him the memory of her mother's voice. The deal sealed, they traveled on together.

At the top of the Shattered Spire, Elara placed her hand on the altar of moonstone. The sky above split open, revealing a second moonÔÇöhidden, dark, and angry. The flame from her village soared into the heavens, lighting the hidden moon. From its light descended a being made of shadows and stars: the last Skykeeper.

The Skykeeper offered Elara a choiceÔÇörestore the broken balance of the moons and guard the world forever, or return home with all her memories and the power to forget the magic. She chose guardianship. Now, on every full moon, a cold blue flame burns where she once stood, whispering new names into the night.
